cs.CV, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with compressed sensing applied to hyperspectral imaging, which involves both image processing and signal processing aspects. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely category, as it covers topics related to image processing and analysis. The paper also proposes a novel architecture for compressive hyperspectral imaging, which involves optimization and reconstruction techniques, making cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely categories as well. Moreover, the paper presents experimental results on real hyperspectral images, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.SI (Signal Processing).
